[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m Find the largest possible real part of \[(75+117i)z+\frac{96+144i}{z}\]where $z$ is a complex number with $|z|=4$.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m Remember to put your answer on its own line after "Answer:".
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m assistant
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m [response] The expression we are trying to maximize is \((75 + 117i)z + \frac{96 + 144i}{z}\) subject to the constraint \(|z| = 4\).
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m Let \(z = 4e^{i\theta}\), where \(\theta\) is a real number. Then, we can rewrite the expression as:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m \[
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m (75 + 117i)4e^{i\theta} + \frac{96 + 144i}{4e^{i\theta}} = 4(75 + 117i)e^{i\theta} + \frac{96 + 144i}{4e^{i\theta}}.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m \]
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m Simplifying, we get:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m \[
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m 4(75 + 117i)e^{i\theta} + \frac{96 + 144i}{4e^{i\theta}} = 4(75 + 117i)e^{i\theta} + \frac{24(4 + 6i)}{4e^{i\theta}} = 4(75 + 117i)e^{i\theta} + \frac{24(4 + 6i)}{4e^{i\theta}} = 4(75 + 117i)e^{i\theta} + \frac{6(4 + 6i)}{e^{i\theta}}.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m \]
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m We can write \(e^{i\theta} = \cos\theta + i\sin\theta\) and \(\frac{1}{e^{i\theta}} = \cos\theta - i\sin\theta\). So, the expression becomes:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m \[
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m 4(75 + 117i)(\cos\theta + i\sin\theta) + 6(4 + 6i)(\cos\theta - i\sin\theta).
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m \]
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m Expanding this, we get:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m \[
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m 4(75\cos\theta - 117\sin\theta) + 4i(75\sin\theta + 117\cos\theta) + 6(4\cos\theta + 6\sin\theta) + 6i(-6\sin\theta + 4\cos\theta).
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m \]
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m Combining the real and imaginary parts, we have:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m \[
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m 4(75\cos\theta - 117\sin\theta) + 6(4\cos\theta + 6\sin\theta) + i(4(75\sin\theta + 117\cos\theta) + 6(-6\sin\theta + 4\cos\theta)).
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m \]
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m Simplifying the real part, we get:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m \[
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m 4(75\cos\theta - 117\sin\theta) + 6(4\cos\theta + 6\sin\theta) = 300\cos\theta - 468\sin\theta + 24\cos\theta + 36\sin\theta = 324\cos\theta - 432\sin\theta.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m \]
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m 
Training Progress:   0%|          | 6/559900 [48:12<69316:21:28, 445.69s/it]
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m To maximize the real part, we need to maximize \(324\cos\theta - 432\sin\theta\). The maximum value of \(a\cos\theta + b\sin\theta\) is \(\sqrt{a^2 + b^2}\). So, the maximum value of \(324\cos\theta - 432\sin\theta\) is \(\sqrt{324^2 + 432^2} = \sqrt{104976 + 186624} = \sqrt{291600} = 540\).
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=151678)[0m Thus, the largest possible real part of \((75 + 117i)z + \frac{96 + 144i}{z}\) is \(\boxed{540}\).
