[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m Please reason step by step, and put your final answer within \boxed{}.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m user
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m Solve the following math problem step by step. The last line of your response should be of the form Answer: $Answer (without quotes) where $Answer is the answer to the problem.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m Find the largest possible real part of \[(75+117i)z+\frac{96+144i}{z}\]where $z$ is a complex number with $|z|=4$.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m Remember to put your answer on its own line after "Answer:".
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m assistant
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m [response] s
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m Answer: $695$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m We start by expressing $z$ in polar form as $z=4(\cos\theta+i\sin\theta)$. The real part of the expression is then \begin{align*}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m \text{Re} \bigg((75+117i)(4\cos\theta+4i\sin\theta)+\frac{96+144i}{4\cos\theta+4i\sin\theta} \bigg) &\qquad \text{Plug in }z\text{ and }z^{-1}.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m \\&=\text{Re} \bigg(4\cos\theta(75+117i)+4i\sin\theta(75+117i)+\frac{96+144i}{4(\cos\theta+i\sin\theta)} \bigg)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m \\&=\text{Re} \bigg(4\cos\theta(75+117i)+4i\sin\theta(75+117i)+(2+3i)(\cos\theta-i\sin\theta) \bigg)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m \\ &=\text{Re} \bigg(200\cos\theta+333i\cos\theta+15i\sin\theta-369\sin\theta \bigg)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m \\ &=200\cos\theta-369\sin\theta.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m \end{align*}Differentiating this expression with respect to $\theta$ and setting it equal to zero gives \begin{align*}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m 200(-\sin\theta)-369(\cos\theta)&=0
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m \\-200\sin\theta-369\cos\theta&=0
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m \\ \tan\theta=-\frac{200}{369}.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m \end{align*}This can occur at two values of $\theta$; we choose the obtuse one because the cosine will then be negative and the sine will be positive, so plugging our values of $\theta$ into this expression gives $\cos\theta=-0.82$ and $\sin\theta=0.57$. The $\max$ is then \begin{align*}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m 200\cos\theta-369\sin\theta&=200(-0.82)-369(0.57)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m \\ &\approx\boxed{-695}.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=181612)[0m \end{align*}
