[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m \[
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m \text{where } z \text{ is a complex number with } |z|=4.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m \]
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m For any complex number \( z \) that satisfies \(|z|=4\), we can write \( z \) in the form \( z = 4e^{i\theta} \), where \(\theta\) is the argument of \( z \).
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m \[
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m z = 4\cos\theta + 4i\sin\theta
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m \]
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m Given this parametrization of \( z \), we need to compute the expression:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m \[
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m f(\theta) = (75+117i)z + \frac{96+144i}{z}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m \]
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m Decompose the problem into:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 1. Multiply \((75+117i)z\)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 2. Compute the conjugate of \(z\), compute \(\frac{96+144i}{z}\)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 3. Extract the real parts and simplify the resulting expression.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m We can time to evaluate and find the maximum real part of this expression by iterating through potential \(\theta\). 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m Let us use Python to iterate through the resulting real parts, orgram:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m ```python
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m import numpy as np
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m # Define the complex constants
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m a = (75 + 117j)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m b = (96 + 144j)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m # Define the function f(theta) to maximize the real part
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m def f(theta):
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m     z = 4 * np.exp(1j * theta)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m     return np.real(a * z + b / z)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m # Iterate over possible values of theta in [0, 2*pi)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m max_real_part = -np.inf
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m best_theta = None
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m resolution = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, 1000)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m for theta in resolution:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m     real_part = f(theta)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m     if real_part > max_real_part:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m         max_real_part = real_part
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m         best_theta = theta
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m print(((best_theta, max_real_part)))
[36m(TaskRunner pid=221696)[0m ```
